%20height%3D%5C%223881%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden%20is%20joined%20by%20Education%20Secretary%20Miguel%20Cardona.%3Cp%3EChip%20Somodevilla%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EHouse%20Republicans%20proposed%20a%20bill%20to%20cut%20funding%20for%20the%20Education%20Department.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20would%20strain%20already%20tight%20resources%20to%20facilitate%20the%20new%20income-driven%20repayment%20plan.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20could%20also%20heighten%20repayment%20challenges%20like%20poor%20customer%20service.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-companies-mohela-punished-borrowers-repayment-servicer-errors-education-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFunding%20cuts%20could%20be%20coming%20for%20the%20Education%20Department%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20key%20programs%20for%20student-loan%20borrowers%20are%20at%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20the%20House%20Appropriations%20Committee%20has%20passed%20seven%20of%20its%2012%20bills%20to%20fund%20federal%20agencies%20in%20the%20upcoming%20fiscal%20year.%20The%20committee%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fappropriations.house.gov%2Fsites%2Frepublicans.appropriations.house.gov%2Ffiles%2FFY24-LHHS-Explanatory-Materials.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereleased%20details%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20one%20of%20the%20remaining%20bills%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Labor%2C%20Health%20and%20Human%20Services%2C%20Education%2C%20and%20Related%20Agencies%20bill%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20proposed%20budget%20cuts%20are%20significant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20Federal%20Student%20Aid%20specifically%2C%20which%20oversees%20student-loan%20repayment%20and%20servicing%2C%20the%20committee's%20cuts%20could%20put%20programs%20many%20borrowers%20rely%20on%20at%20risk.%20The%20committee%20wants%20to%20fund%20FSA%20at%20%241.8%20billion%2C%20which%20is%20%24264%20million%20below%20its%20current%20level%20and%20nearly%20%24884%20million%20below%20what%20Biden%20requested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20targeted%20a%20range%20of%20the%20Education%20Department's%20recent%20initiatives%20to%20provide%20relief%20to%20borrowers%2C%20including%20streamlining%20the%20process%20for%20borrower%20defense%20to%20repayment%2C%20which%20is%20a%20program%20that%20allows%20borrowers%20to%20file%20claims%20if%20they%20believe%20they%20were%20defrauded%20by%20the%20school%20they%20attended%2C%20and%20if%20approved%2C%20their%20loans%20would%20be%20wiped%20out.%20The%20GOP%20lawmakers%20said%20their%20bills%20includes%20legislative%20language%20%26quot%3Bprohibiting%20funding%26quot%3B%20for%20improving%20that%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20committee%20said%20it%20would%20not%20include%20more%20funding%20to%20facilitate%20the%20department's%20new%20SAVE%20income-driven%20repayment%20plan%20intended%20to%20make%20monthly%20payments%20cheaper%20for%20borrowers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20funding%20cuts%20would%20come%20just%20over%20a%20month%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-repayment-issues-debt-relief-broken-industry-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20student-loan%20borrowers'%20return%20to%20repayment%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20an%20over%20three-year%20pause.%20In%20October%2C%20borrowers'%20bills%20starting%20becoming%20due%20again%2C%20and%20millions%20of%20them%20have%20been%20faced%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-bills-are-wrong-borrowers-servicers-fixing-errors-education-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20range%20of%20errors%20including%20late%20billing%20statements%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20inaccurate%20information%20on%20their%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20servicers%20and%20the%20Education%20Department%20have%20previously%20noted%20that%20increased%20funding%20for%20FSA%20is%20crucial%20to%20ensure%20there%20are%20sufficient%20resources%20to%20manage%20the%20unprecedented%20transition%20back%20into%20repayment.%20The%20GOP%20appropriations%20lawmakers%2C%20however%2C%20wrote%20that%20the%20%26quot%3BDepartment%20diverted%20taxpayer%20resources%20for%20its%20partisan%2C%20costly%20student%20loan%20policies%2C%20when%20it%20needed%20to%20be%20preparing%20for%20an%20orderly%20resumption%20of%20Federal%20student%20loan%20payments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Department%20repeatedly%20delayed%20the%20return%20to%20loan%20repayment%2C%20which%20generated%20uncertainty%20and%20undermined%20a%20timely%20and%20orderly%20restart%20of%20loan%20payments%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETop%20Republican%20on%20the%20House%20education%20committee%20Virginia%20Foxx%20also%20previously%20told%20Insider%20she%20did%20not%20think%20FSA%20needed%20more%20funding%20to%20ensure%20things%20run%20smoothly%20for%20borrowers%2C%20saying%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20department%20needs%20to%20live%20within%20its%20means%20and%20be%20fortunate%20that%20it%20has%20the%20funding%20that%20it%20has%20right%20now%20because%20every%20department%20in%20the%20federal%20government%20is%20overfunded%2C%20in%20my%20opinion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%2C%20the%20issue%20of%20funding%20remains%20a%20top%20concern.%20Deputy%20Under%20Secretary%20of%20Education%20Ben%20Miller%20said%20during%20a%20debt%20relief%20negotiation%20session%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20department's%20been%20seeking%20funding%20increases%20for%20Federal%20Student%20Aid%20and%20we%20are%20not%20in%20the%20position%20where%20we%20have%20significant%20resources%20to%20add%20large%20numbers%20of%20staff%2C%20either%20in%20house%20or%20on%20a%20contract%20basis%2C%20to%20do%20lots%20of%20additional%20work%20streams.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-cheaper-payments-at-risk-borrowers-budget-cuts-2023-11%5C%22%3