%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSomeone%20couldn't%20resist%20chiming%20in%2C%20'So%20it's%20a%20cricket%20boundary%2C%20is%20it%3F'%26quot%3B%20the%2045-year-old%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20all%20laughed%20except%20for%20me.%20I%20just%20felt%20like%20something%20passed%20by%20me%20and%20I%20couldn't%20quite%20catch%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20%26quot%3Bhome%20run%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20US%20refers%20to%20a%20successful%20result%2C%20the%20baseball%20analogy%20didn't%20land%20with%20a%20UK%20audience%20that%20was%20unfamiliar%20with%20the%20sport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarton%20said%20that%20mistakes%20weren't%20always%20trivial%2C%20%26quot%3Bespecially%20in%20sectors%20like%20finance%2C%20where%20details%20matter%2C%20a%20simple%20misunderstanding%20could%20be%20costly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20he's%20had%20to%20pick%20up%20British%20slang%20to%20succeed%20in%20the%20financial%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20once%20had%20an%20initial%20blanked-out-face%20moment%20when%20I%20heard%20something%20was%20'5%2C000%20quid%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20in%20all%2C%20these%20slips%20are%20very%20fun%2C%20but%20if%20you're%20unsure%20about%20what's%20being%20said%2C%20ask%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20the%20one%20talking%2C%20offer%20a%20quick%20explanation%20of%20your%20colloquialisms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20American%20sayings%20have%20dark%20histories%2C%20so%20be%20aware%20of%20explaining%20them%20to%20Brits%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESharon%20Klahr%20Coey%2C%20a%20writer%20and%20editor%2C%20moved%20to%20London%20from%20New%20York%20City%20nearly%2020%20years%20ago%20and%20still%20mistakenly%20uses%20American%20phrases%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20surprised%20that%20some%20of%20the%20phrases%20she%20used%20in%20America%20weren't%20understood%20there.%20When%20she%20had%20to%20explain%20their%20origins%2C%20she%20realized%20how%20%26quot%3Bhorrible%20and%20insensitive%26quot%3B%20they%20were%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20commented%20once%20about%20'drinking%20the%20Kool-Aid%2C'%20which%20is%20an%20expression%20used%20to%20denote%20abject%20obedience%2C%20often%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20in%20really%20believing%20in%20the%20product%20or%20culture%20even%20if%20it's%20a%20bit%20dubious%2C%26quot%3B%20the%2053-year-old%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20went%20over%20my%20British%20coworkers'%20heads%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BAs%20I%20explained%20it%20comes%20from%20the%20Jonestown%20massacre%2C%20where%20members%20of%20the%20cult%20drank%20poisoned%C2%A0Flavor%20Aid%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0similar%20to%20the%20powdered%20drink%20Kool-Aid%20that%20exists%20now%20%E2%80%94%20and%20died%2C%20it%20occurred%C2%A0to%20me%20this%20shouldn't%20be%20a%20funny%2C%20off-handed%20comment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20remembered%20using%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3Bgoing%20postal%2C%26quot%3B%20used%20in%20America%20to%20describe%20feeling%20really%20angry%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20having%20to%20explain%20it%2C%20the%20horror%20of%20this%20flip%20comment%20hit%20me%20as%20well%20as%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20mid-80s%2C%20there%20were%20a%20spate%20of%20US%20postal%20workers%20having%20enough%20and%20mass%20murdering%20people%20in%20the%20post%20office%20with%20shotguns.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Pants'%20is%20not%20an%20appropriate%20word%20for%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20lighter%20note%2C%20she%20remembers%20complimenting%20a%20coworker%20on%20her%20cute%20pants.%20Klahr%20Coey%20was%20talking%20about%20her%20peer's%20trousers%2C%20but%20the%20coworker%20thought%20she%20was%20complimenting%20her%20underwear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20gasped%20and%20reached%20her%20hand%20around%20to%20her%20back%20to%20make%20sure%20her%20trousers%20hadn't%20fallen%20down%20exposing%20her%20underwear%2C%26quot%3B%20Klahr%20Coey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20most%20cases%2C%20she%20said%20misunderstandings%20hadn't%20proved%20a%20problem%2C%20adding%20that%20she'd%20learned%20to%20%26quot%3Bmake%20life%20easier%26quot%3B%20and%20speak%20in%20a%20way%20people%20at%20work%20understood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBe%20specific%20with%20your%20vocabulary%20about%20types%20of%20calls%20and%20meetings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJennifer%20Cairns%2C%20who%20works%20for%20the%20advocacy%20group%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ladyrebelclub.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ELady%20Rebel%20Club%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20lived%20in%20Northern%20Ireland%20for%2025%20years.%20She%20listed%20several%20phrases%20that%20still%20slipped%20out%20at%20work%2C%20including%20%26quot%3Bshoot%20the%20breeze%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bdiscombobulated%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bpissed%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0angry%2C%20not%20drunk.%20Her%20colleagues%20often%20respond%20with%20a%20stare%20of%20confusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20learned%20that%20when%20she%20said%20she%20would%20%26quot%3Bcall%20for%26quot%3B%20a%20team%20member%2C%20they%20expected%20her%20to%20show%20up%20in%20person%20for%20a%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20US%2C%20it%20means%20'I%20will%20phone%20you%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20learned%20that%20the%20hard%20way%20when%20I%20didn't%20show%20up%20for%20a%20meeting%20many%20years%20ago.%20Now%20I%20say%20we%20can%20video%20chat%2C%20Zoom%2C%20or%20I'll%20ring%20you%20verses%20using%20the%20word%20'call.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Quite%20nice'%20can%20be%20understood%20as%20an%20insult%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Telfer%20and%20his%20wife%20moved%20to%20Scotland%20from%20the%20US%20in%202019%20to%20be%20closer%20to%20family.%20When%20he%20started%20working%20within%20the%20National%20Health%20Service%2C%20the%20culture%20gap%20became%20evident%20in%20the%20language%20he%20used%20with%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETelfer%20said%20he%20would%20write%20his%20numerical%20dates%20month%2C%20day%2C%20and%20year%2C%20but%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20the%20day%20comes%20first.%20He%20now%20just%20says%20and%20writes%20any%20dates%20using%20the%20full%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20the%20biggest%20issues%20come%20not%20from%20specific%20words%20but%20different%20connotations%2C%26quot%3B%20the%2039-year-old%20founder%20of%20the%20fitness%20startup%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwildstrong.co%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EWildStrong%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20example%2C%20in%20America%2C%20'quite%20nice'%20can%20be%20a%20modifier%20that%20implies%20something%20is%20very%20nice.%20Whereas%20in%20UK%20English%2C%20saying%20something%20is%20quite%20nice%20could%20imply%20that%20it's%20underwhelming%20or%20not%20good%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20once%20got%20in%20trouble%20for%20calling%20somebody's%20gift%20'quite%20nice%2C'%20which%C2%A0I%20meant%20as%20a%20hearty%20compliment%20but%20was%20interpreted%20as%20an%20insult.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETelfer%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20find%20that%20most%20people%20are%20good-natured%20about%20misunderstandings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-phrases-british-people-dont-understand-at-work-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699437818000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654a13f036d588dc55cbfccf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-phrases-british-people-dont-understand-at-work-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Americans%20who've%20moved%20to%20the%20UK%20share%20the%20things%20they%20say%20at%20work%20that%20most%20confuse%20their%20British%20colleagues.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Lauren%20Crosby%20Medlicott)%22%2C%22enga