%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsee-questions-bridgewater-test-ray-dalio-principles-the-fund-book-2023-11%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBridgewater%20Associates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20hundreds%20of%20employees%20had%20their%20own%20personal%20so-called%20baseball%20cards%2C%20which%20featured%20dots%2C%20or%20numbers%2C%20rating%20them%20on%20a%201-to-10%20scale%2C%20the%20book%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpost%2Fpreview%3Fsvapi%26post_id%3D6548f365b0b368bea73d848e%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERob%20Copeland's%20%26quot%3BThe%20Fund%3A%20Ray%20Dalio%2C%20Bridgewater%20Associates%2C%20and%20the%20Unraveling%20of%20a%20Wall%20Street%20Legend%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20released%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20and%20it%20details%20some%20of%20what%20Copeland%20found%20out%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fbridgewater-ray-dalio-radical-transparency-app-dots-2017-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erating%20system%20for%20all%20Bridgewater%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInformation%20was%20compiled%20into%20individual%20employee%20profiles%2C%20which%20were%20known%20as%20baseball%20cards%20around%20the%20office%2C%20the%20book%20said.%20Workers%20were%20each%20judged%20in%20the%20same%20categories%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20baseball%20cards%20were%20public%20for%20all%20to%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20colleagues%20rated%20one%20another%20in%20real%20time%2C%20a%20tendency%20emerged%20to%20pile%20onto%20those%20with%20lower%20scores%20and%20do%20everything%20possible%20to%20align%20with%20those%20ranked%20highly%2C%20according%20to%20the%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForgetting%20to%20stock%20up%20the%20office%20sodas%20would%20bring%20a%20storm%20of%20negative%20ratings%20for%20the%20employee%20responsible%20%E2%80%94%20and%20assistants%20would%20receive%20low%20scores%20if%20their%20bosses%20were%20late%20to%20a%20meeting%2C%20the%20book%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBus%20drivers%20would%20be%20investigated%20if%20they%20kept%20the%20bus%20too%20cool%20or%20too%20warm%2C%20even%20though%20different%20employees%20might%20submit%20different%20complaints%20based%20on%20personal%20preferences%2C%20according%20to%20%26quot%3BThe%20Fund.%26quot%3B%20And%20employees%20were%20recorded%20during%20meetings%20to%20later%20be%20assessed%20%E2%80%94%20a%20practice%20that%20was%20common%20under%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fbridgewater-bob-prince-culture-performance-2017-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Dalio's%20principles%20for%20running%20a%20successful%20company%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDalio%20would%20pause%20meetings%20to%20conduct%20polls%20on%20whether%20or%20not%20a%20particular%20employee%20was%20doing%20their%20job%20well%2C%20the%20book%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Partington%2C%20a%20recruiting%20manager%20earning%20more%20than%20%242%20million%20a%20year%20when%20he%20started%20at%20the%20company%2C%20was%20subjected%20to%20such%20public%20assessments%2C%20according%20to%20the%20book.%20Partington%20was%20tasked%20with%20bringing%20Bridgewater%20%26quot%3Bto%20the%20promised%20land%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20book%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20one%20year%20in%20his%20position%2C%20Dalio%20sent%20out%20a%20poll%20to%20the%20entire%20company%3A%20%26quot%3BDoes%20Michael%20Partington%20add%20value%3F%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20his%20question%20was%20met%20with%20negative%20responses%2C%20Dalio%20cut%20Partington's%20salary%20in%20half%2C%20the%20book%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20haven't%20taken%20us%20to%20the%20promised%20land%2C%26quot%3B%20Dalio%20told%20him%2C%20according%20to%20the%20book.%20Partington%20was%20later%20fired%20by%20the%20Bridgewater%20founder%20after%20less%20than%20five%20years%2C%20the%20book%20said.%20Partington%20didn't%20comment%20in%20the%20book.%20He%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20requ