%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F08104925%2FScreenshot-2023-11-08-at-10.49.18%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarly%20on%20in%20Jayant%20Digambar%20Somalkar%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESthal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%20four%20men%20can%20be%20seen%20discussing%20a%20woman%E2%80%99s%20complexion.%20%E2%80%9CShe%20seems%20fair%2C%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20she%3F%E2%80%9D%20one%20of%20them%20asks%2C%20only%20to%20be%20shut%20down%20by%20the%20other%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20all%20make-up.%20Didn%E2%80%99t%20you%20notice%20her%20elbows%3F%20They%20gave%20it%20away.%E2%80%9D%20The%20woman%2C%20actually%20a%20young%20girl%20named%20Savita%20(Nandini%20Chikte)%2C%20barely%20out%20of%20her%20teens%2C%20in%20her%20final%20year%20of%20college%20pursuing%20B.A%20(Sociology)%2C%20is%20being%20looked%20at%20as%20a%20prospective%20bride.%20Those%20men%20could%20be%20talking%20about%20livestock.%20Such%20is%20the%20%E2%80%98marketplace%E2%80%99%20for%20arranged%20marriages%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20in%20India%2C%20where%20such%20casual%20indignities%20are%20fair%20game.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F3qQADbYafM0%3Fsi%3DTqL0gZI-CNVqs24c%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20bunch%20of%20callous%20traditions%20reduce%20the%20brides%E2%80%99%20identities%20to%20their%20responses%20to%20a%20robotic%20questionnaire%20like%20this%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%E2%80%99s%20your%20full%20name%3F%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%E2%80%99s%20your%20height%3F%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%E2%80%99s%20your%20mother%E2%80%99s%20native%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20have%20you%20studied%3F%20Do%20you%20work%20in%20the%20field%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20might%20as%20well%20be%20called%20%E2%80%98recruiting%E2%80%99%20a%20daughter-in-law.%20Debutante%20Somalkar%20mines%20the%20scene%20for%20all%20its%20awkwardness%2C%20unintentional%20humour%20derived%20from%20inane%20rituals%2C%20and%20observes%20the%20transactionality%20around%20them.%20It%E2%80%99s%20no%20secret%20then%20that%20during%20a%20key%20scene%2C%20a%20character%20can%20be%20heard%20haggling%20for%20brinjals%20at%20a%20vegetable%20market%20while%20also%20simultaneously%20negotiating%20the%20dowry%20he%20expects%20from%20the%20bride%E2%80%99s%20father.%20The%20scene%20is%20chillingly%20matter-of-fact.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDaulatrao%20Wandhare%20(Taranath%20Khitekar)%20is%20a%20cotton%20farmer%20in%20rural%20Maharashtra.%20As%20life%20goes%20on%20in%20this%20part%20of%20the%20world%2C%20he%E2%80%99s%20expected%20to%20start%20looking%20for%20a%20match%20for%20his%20daughter%2C%20Savita.%20It%E2%80%99s%20largely%20because%20of%20the%20societal%20pressure%20to%20conform%20to%20ancient%20thinking%2C%20garbed%20in%20concepts%20like%20%E2%80%98tradition%E2%80%99.%20Somalkar%20and%20editor%20Abhijit%20Deshpande%20bring%20a%20nice%20rhythm%20to%20these%20sequences%20where%20the%20boy%E2%80%99s%20side%20comes%20to%20Daulatrao%E2%80%99s%20home.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20kind%20of%20musicality%20to%20the%20rituals%20like%20a%20bucket%20of%20fresh%20water%20being%20kept%20ready%20for%20the%20guests%20to%20wash%20their%20hands%2C%20feet%20and%20face%2C%20and%20a%20new%20towel%20offered%20to%20them%20to%20wipe%20themselves.%20There%E2%80%99s%20also%20the%20small%20talk%20in%20between%20the%20chai%2C%20poha%20and%20supari%20being%20offered%20to%20the%20guests.%20The%20faux%20respect%20among%20the%20men%20is%20followed%20by%20the%20most%20disrespectful%2C%20condescending%20tone%20while%20%E2%80%98interviewing%E2%80%99%20the%20bride.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20umpteen%20films%20on%20how%20rigged%20the%20system%20of%20arranged%20marriage%20in%20India%20is%20in%20the%20groom%E2%80%99s%20favour%2C%20how%20Indian%20society%20is%20deeply%20patriarchal%2C%20and%20yet%20Somalkar%E2%80%99s%20film%20never%20feels%20tedious.%20It%E2%80%99s%20because%20of%20the%20specificity%20of%20the%20world%20that%20Somalkar%20has%20chosen%20%E2%80%93%20it%E2%80%99s%20full%20of%20rich%2C%20tiny%20observations.%20Like%20that%20throwaway%20mention%20of%20Daulatrao%E2%80%99s%20academically-disinclined%20son%2C%20Mangya%20(Suyog%20Dhawas)%20and%20his%20budding%20cricket%20career.%20Unlike%20many%20of%20his%20peers%2C%20Mangya%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20afford%20to%20pursue%20his%20passion%20for%20cricket%2C%20and%20being%20unfit%20for%20a%20job%20relegates%20him%20to%20working%20on%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20field%2C%20watching%20IPL%20and%20betting%20money%20in%20the%20fantasy%20cricket%20league.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20time%20when%204G%20seems%20to%20have%20reached%20most%20villages%2C%20but%20sensibilities%20have%20progressed%20very%20little%20since%20perhaps%20medieval%20times.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F08111355%2FScreenshot-2023-11-08-at-10.55.2.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F08111355%2FScreenshot-2023-11-08-at-10.55.2.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F08111355%2FScreenshot-2023-11-08-at-10.55.2-300x159.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F08111355%2FScreenshot-2023-11-08-at-10.55.2-1024x542.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684043%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22635%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20still%20from%20%E2%80%98Sthal%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20Savita%20is%20a%20dutiful%20student.%20She%20uses%20the%20money%20she%20gets%20for%20to%20buy%20books%20for%20public%20service%20exams%2C%20while%20intermittently%20being%20humiliated%2C%20as%20almost%20a%20a%20ritual%2C%20each%20time%20a%20prospective%20groom%20visits.%20She%E2%80%99s%20intellectually%20curious%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20implied%20by%20scenes%20showing%20her%20in%20the%20college%20library%20reading%20the%20newspapers.%20She%20feels%20the%20injustice%20she%E2%80%99s%20being%20subjected%20to%E2%80%94and%20slowly%20forms%20a%20vocabulary%20to%20articulate%20herself.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChikte%20is%20very%20impressive%20as%20Savita%2C%20playing%20her%20with%20a%20meekness%20at%20first%2C%20which%20slowly%20churns%20into%20resolve%20and%20ultimately%20rebellion.%20However%2C%20the%20highlight%20of%20the%20film%20is%20Khitekar%20%E2%80%93%20as%20the%20father%20of%20the%20prospective%20bride.%20He%20maintains%20this%20stooped%2C%20stoic%20body-language%20throughout%20the%20film%2C%20almost%20as%20if%20he%E2%80%99s%20being%20crushed%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20many%20worlds.%20Somalkar%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20take%20the%20easy%20way%20out%20by%20portraying%20Daulatrao%20to%20be%20the%20strict%2C%20uncompromising%20paterfamilias.%20Instead%20Khitekar%E2%80%99s%20face%20communicates%20the%20pain%2C%20shame%20and%20the%20relentless%20injustice%20he%20has%20to%20endure%20%E2%80%93%20as%20a%20farmer%20and%20also%20as%20the%20father%20of%20a%20girl%20in%20a%20shamelessly%20patriarchal%20society.%20A%20crucial%20scene%20%E2%80%93%20when%20he%20has%20to%20tell%20his%20daughter%20to%20forgo%20the%20public%20service%20exams%20because%20a%20prospective%20groom%20will%20come%20to%20see%20her%20%E2%80%93%20is%20a%20masterclass%20in%20tenderness%2C%20parental%20concern%20and%20insecurity%20trumping%20cold%20logic.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESthal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20not%20the%20most%20novel%20story%20to%20emerge%20out%20of%20India%2C%20but%20Somalkar%20tells%20it%20in%20a%20measured%20way.%20It%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20forensic%20gaze%20of%20Chaitanya%20Tamhane%20or%20the%20fluent%20vigour%20of%20Nagraj%20Manjule%20%E2%80%93%20but%20it%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20an%20overstatement%20to%20include%20Somalkar%20among%20the%20wave%20of%20interesting%20Marathi%20filmmakers%20in%20the%20past%20decade.%20It%E2%80%99s%20visible%20in%20the%20way%20he%20sparingly%20employs%20score%20(by%20Madhav%20Agarwal%20and%20Tamara%20Kazziha)%20and%20slow-motion%20to%20heighten%20the%20expression%20of%20earnest%2C%20idealistic%20puppy%20love%20and%20then%20disrupts%20it%20with%20real-world%20choices.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESomalkar%E2%80%99s%20film%20reminded%20me%20of%20Jeo%20Baby%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Great%20Indian%20Kitchen%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(2020)%20%E2%80%93%20indicting%20the%20apathy%20of%20a%20society%20by%20being%20a%20silent%20observer%20to%20injustices%20hidden%20in%20plain%20sight.%20Patriarchy%20is%20bad.%20Equality%20is%20worth%20striving%20for.%20Many%20films%20have%20preached%20this%2C%20many%20more%20will%20continue%20to.%20But%20it%20will%20always%20be%20refreshing%20to%20see%20films%20reflect%20on%20how%20deeply%20these%20things%20are%20embedded%20in%20our%20most%20mundane%20choices%20and%20circumstances.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E*%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESthal%20premiered%20at%20the%202023%20Toronto%20International%20Film%20Festival%20(TIFF)%2C%20recently%20had%20its%20India%20premiere%20at%20the%202023%20MAMI%20Mumbai%20International%20Film%20Festival%2C%20and%20is%20currently%20playing%20at%20the%20Dhar