%20US%20Army%20faces%20as%20it%20grapples%20with%20designing%20a%20next-generation%20tank%20that%20can%20fight%20in%20both%20Europe%20and%20the%20Pacific.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERivals%20in%20both%20theaters%20%E2%80%94%20chiefly%20Russia%20and%20China%20%E2%80%94%20have%20studied%20US%20armored%20vehicles%20and%20the%20way%20they're%20used%20and%20are%20fielding%20weapons%20to%20counter%20them.%20The%20Army's%20main%20battle%20tank%2C%20the%20M1%20Abrams%2C%20now%20faces%20two%20main%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20is%20that%20it's%20an%20aging%20Cold%20War%20design.%20%26quot%3BThe%20M1%20Abrams%20will%20not%20dominate%20the%202040%20battlefield%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Army%20Science%20Board%2C%20a%20scientific%20advisory%20body%2C%20warned%20in%20a%20recent%20report%20on%20next-generation%20armored%20vehicles.%20%26quot%3BAll%20of%20the%20M1's%20advantages%20in%20mobility%2C%20firepower%20and%20protection%20are%20at%20risk.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20is%20that%20the%2070-ton%20Abrams%20is%20designed%20to%20fight%20on%20the%20plains%20of%20Europe%2C%20not%20the%20jungles%20and%20remote%20islands%20of%20the%20Pacific.%20%26quot%3BLogistics%20and%20support%2C%20difficult%20in%20both%20theaters%2C%20are%20exacerbated%20by%20the%20Indo-Pacific's%20longer%20distances%20and%20less%20developed%20infrastructure%2C%20including%20ports%20and%20airfields%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsherman-pershing-abrams-tanks-used-by-the-us-army-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EM1%20was%20originally%20designed%20in%20the%20mid-1970s%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20is%20due%20for%20replacement%20as%20the%20US%20military%20adapts%20to%20an%20era%20in%20which%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-ukraine-fighting-drone-war-us-military-was-waiting-for-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eweapons%20like%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprecision-artillery-shells-aid-ukraine-in-artillery-battle-with-russia-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmart%20artillery%20shells%3C%2Fa%3E%20pose%20new%20threats%20to%20armored%20vehicles.%20But%20even%20as%20rivals%20upgrade%20their%20tanks%20and%20anti-tank%20weapons%2C%20it%20may%20be%20an%20immense%20challenge%20for%20US%20planners%20to%20agree%20on%20what%20a%20tank%20fit%20for%20global%20operations%20looks%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERestricted%20terrain%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221780%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22XM-1%20Abrams%20tanks%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654a43dbb788914e5551820d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221331%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20XM-1%20Abrams%2C%20which%20would%20replace%20the%20M60%20tank%2C%20at%20Fort%20Knox%20in%20Kentucky%20in%201979.%3Cp%3EUS%20Defense%20Department%2FEddie%20McCrossan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETanks%20have%20always%20been%20Western-centric.%20They%20were%20invented%20by%20Britain%2C%20were%20the%20leading%20edge%20of%20the%20Nazi%20blitzkrieg%2C%20and%20were%20manufactured%20in%20enormous%20quantities%20by%20Russia%20and%20America.%20Israel's%20Western-style%20army%20uses%20tanks%20proficiently%2C%20while%20armor%20is%20still%20one%20of%20the%20key%20weapons%20in%20the%20Russo-Ukraine%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20Pacific%20wars%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20both%20on%20islands%20and%20continental%20East%20Asia%2C%20tanks%20often%20played%20a%20secondary%20role%20in%20what%20were%20mostly%20infantry%20battles%20fought%20on%20rough%2C%20roadless%20terrain%20or%20on%20beaches%20and%20surf%20zones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJapan%20did%20use%20a%20small%20number%20of%20armored%20vehicles%20against%20poorly%20armed%20Chinese%20troops%20in%20the%20Sino-Japanese%20War%20of%201937-1945.%20British%20troops%20in%201942%20were%20shocked%20when%20Japanese%20armor%20advanced%20through%20the%20%26quot%3Bimpenetrable%26quot%3B%20jungle%20on%20the%20Malay%20Peninsula.%20During%20the%20island-hopping%20campaign%20of%201942-1945%2C%20US%20Army%20tanks%20provided%20valuable%20fire%20support%20against%20entrenched%20Japanese%20defenders%20(and%20performed%20a%20similar%20role%20in%20the%20Korean%20and%20Vietnam%20wars.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday's%20US%20Army%20is%20fully%20aware%20of%20the%20value%20of%20tanks%20as%20part%20of%20a%20combined-arms%20team%2C%20even%20in%20a%20theater%20unfriendly%20to%20armor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22M1A1%20Abrams%20tank%20refueling%20Kuwait%20Iraq%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654a43cc3cc84b4dfafda4ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221285%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20M1A1%20Abrams%20at%20a%20refueling%20point%20in%20the%20Kuwaiti%20desert%20near%20the%20Iraqi%20border%20in%20December%202002.%3Cp%3EScott%20Nelson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTank%20and%20armor%20capabilities%20in%20the%20Pacific%20is%20absolutely%20necessary%20for%20conducting%20operations%20in%20restricted%20terrain%2C%26quot%3B%20Gen.%20Charles%20Flynn%2C%20commander%20of%20US%20Army%20Pacific%2C%20told%20reporters%20in%20September.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20there%20is%20plenty%20of%20restricted%20terrain%20out%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20doesn't%20mean%20%26quot%3Bvehicles%20must%20be%20tailored%20for%20individual%20theaters%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Army%20Science%20Board%20noted.%20But%20if%20the%20Army%20is%20serious%20about%20preparing%20for%20Pacific%20conflict%2C%20fifth-generation%20combat%20vehicles%20%E2%80%94%20the%20replacements%20for%20the%20Abrams%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Bradley%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicle%20%E2%80%94%20will%20have%20to%20light%20enough%20to%20be%20easily%20transported%20and%20supplied%20by%20sea%20and%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20description%20hardly%20applies%20to%20the%20Army's%20current%20armor%20force%2C%20which%20was%20designed%20to%20fight%20masses%20of%20Soviet%20tanks%20as%20they%20charged%20through%20the%20Fulda%20Gap%20between%20East%20and%20West%20Germany.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20best%20tank%20is%20useless%20if%20it%20can't%20reach%20the%20battlefield.%20The%20Army%20Science%20Board%20cites%20a%20Center%20for%20Army%20Analysis%20war%20game%20that%20%26quot%3Bdemonstrated%20armor's%20value%20in%20Taiwan's%20defense%2C%20but%20struggles%20with%20deployment%20and%20sustainment%20precluded%20US%20armor's%20arrival%20in%20sufficient%20numbers%20before%20China%20achieved%20a%20fait%20accompli.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EEnd%20of%20the%20Abrams%20era%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221401%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Abrams%20tank%20destroyed%20Iraq%20Baghdad%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654a48a6b788914e555184e1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221050%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20Abrams%20tank%20that%20Iraqi%20officials%20said%20was%20destroyed%20in%20fighting%20south%20of%20Baghdad%20in%20April%202003.%3Cp%3EKARIM%20SAHIB%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20America's%20pivot%20to%20the%20Pacific%2C%20the%20Abrams's%20days%20were%20numbered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20M1%20is%20vulnerable%20to%20drones%20as%20well%20as%20top-attack%20anti-tank%20missiles%2C%20and%20its%20armor%20might%20be%20penetrated%20by%20the%20125-mm%20guns%20on%20Russia's%20T-90%20and%20China's%20Type%2099%20tanks%2C%20the%20Army%20Science%20Board%20found.%20Too%20many%20Abrams%20are%20sidelined%20by%20maintenance%20issues%2C%20but%20even%20if%20enough%20were%20available%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20M1%20at%2070%20tons%20or%20greater%20is%20not%20tactically%2C%20operationally%2C%20or%20strategically%20mobile%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetrofitting%20tanks%20with%20new%20technologies%2C%20such%20as%20robotics%20and%20automation%2C%20would%20be%20as%20useless%20as%20expecting%20that%20%26quot%3Bnew%20technology%20will%20maximally%20improve%20a%201980s%20commercial%20vehicle%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20argued.%20Bolting%20new%20tech%20onto%20an%20aging%20tank%20would%20also%20do%20little%20to%20counter%20advances%20in%20anti-tank%20guided%20missiles%2C%20such%20as%20China's%20Red%20Arrow%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20neither%20do%20Army%20experts%20believe%20that%20autonomous%20robot%20tanks%20will%20be%20a%20viable%20alternative%20by%202040.%20That%20means%20America's%20next-generation%20tank%20will%20have%20to%20be%20a%20manned%20vehicle%20that%20is%20lighter%20than%20the%20Abrams%20but%20with%20better%20protection%20against%20advanced%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221240%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20Army%20threats%20to%20Abrams%20tank%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654a489236d588dc55cc11f3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22784%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThreats%20to%20the%20Abrams%20tank's%20battlefield%20dominance%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Army%20Science%20Board.%3Cp%3EThe%20Army%20Science%20Board%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Army%20Science%20Board%20assessed%20various%20alternatives.%20A%2060-ton%20tank%20with%20a%20130-mm%20gun%20and%20a%20three-person%20crew%3F%20Not%20mobile%20enough.%20A%2040-ton%20light%20tank%20with%20a%20heavy%20cannon%3F%20Not%20enough%20protection.%20The%20study%20did%20seem%20intrigued%20by%20a%20%26quot%3Brobotic%20wingman%26quot%3B%20concept%20of%20a%2030-ton%20vehicle%2C%20armed%20with%20a%20hypervelocity%20missile%2C%20that%20would%20accompany%20manned%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Army%20has%20spent%20two%20decades%20searching%20for%20next-generation%20armor%2C%20dating%20back%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnationalinterest.org%2Fblog%2Fbuzz%2Fus-arm