0Indian%20Armed%20Forces%2C%20the%20Era%20of%20Moscow-Supplied%20Platforms%20and%20Assets%20Is%20Ending%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F22184843%2FSukhoi_Su-30MKI_India_-_Air_Force_AN1234411.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChandigarh%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20phasing%20out%20last%20week%20of%20two%20Russian%20military%20aircraft%20types%20from%20the%20Indian%20armed%20forces%20inventory%20definitively%20presages%20the%20end%20of%20the%20era%20when%20Moscow-supplied%20fixed-wing%20combat%2C%20surveillance%20and%20transport%20platforms%20and%20assorted%20rotary-wing%20assets%20monopolised%20the%20catalogues%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20three%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2031%2C%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20(IAF)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fmig-21-squadron-retired-curtain-closing-iaf-most-abiding-fighter%5C%22%3Eretired%3C%2Fa%3E%20one%20of%20its%20three%20remaining%20upgraded%20MiG-21%20%E2%80%98Bison%E2%80%99%20fighter%20squadrons%2C%20the%20same%20day%20that%20the%20Indian%20Navy%20(IN)%20decommissioned%2C%20after%2044%20years%2C%20the%20last%20of%20its%20five%20Ilyushin%20IL-38%20Sea%20Dragon%20long-range%20maritime%20patrol%20aircraft%20from%20the%20same%20epoch.%20The%20IAF%20also%20aims%2C%20by%202025%2C%20to%20superannuate%20its%20two%20remaining%20MiG-21%20%E2%80%98Bison%E2%80%99%20squadrons%20of%20some%2040%20fighters%2C%20all%20of%20which%20had%20been%20imaginatively%20exploited%20by%20three%20generations%20of%20fighter%20pilots.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20MiG-21s%20will%20be%20imminently%20replaced%20by%20the%20indigenous%20Tejas%20Light%20Combat%20Aircraft%20(LCA)%2C%20while%20the%20IL-38s%20already%20have%20two%20substitutes%20in%20place%3A%2012%20Boeing%20P-8I%20Neptune%20long-range%20maritime%20multi-mission%20platforms%20and%2026%20German-origin%20turboprop%20Dornier%20Do-228s%2C%20licence-built%20by%20Hindustan%20Aeronautics%20Limited%20(HAL)%20in%20Bangalore%20with%20refurbished%20engines%2C%20composite%20propellers%2C%20advanced%20avionics%20and%20a%20glass%20cockpit.%20Another%2012%20Do-228%20maritime%20variants%20were%20presently%20on%20order%20from%20HAL%20by%20the%20IN.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20now%20little%20or%20no%20likelihood%20of%20India%20acquiring%20any%20more%20Russian%20military%20aircraft%2C%E2%80%9D%20declared%20a%20former%20three-star%20IAF%20fighter%20pilot.%20He%20said%20that%20other%20than%20intrinsic%20handicaps%20of%20low%20serviceability%20and%20crippling%20maintenance%20issues%2C%20Moscow%E2%80%99s%20previously%20questionable%20reliability%20in%20providing%20after-sales%20support%2C%20including%20spares%2C%20for%20its%20in-service%20aerial%20platforms%20had%20now%20%E2%80%98multiplied%20exponentially%E2%80%99%20following%20US-led%20sanctions%20for%20invading%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20cross-section%20of%20serving%20and%20retired%20military%20officers%20concurred%20that%20the%20%E2%80%98golden%20age%E2%80%99%20of%20Soviet%2F%20Russian%20aerial%20military%20platforms%20that%20began%20in%201963%20with%20the%20induction%20of%20the%20single-engine%2C%20single-seat%20MiG-21FL%20%E2%80%98Fishbed%E2%80%99%20fighters%20into%20the%20IAF%2C%20and%20was%20thereafter%20supplemented%20by%20a%20vast%20panoply%20of%20other%20platforms%2C%20was%20finally%20drawing%20to%20a%20close.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEven%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20defence%20industrial%20complex%20itself%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20after%20the%20imposition%20of%20sanctions%2021%20months%20ago%2C%20had%20publicly%20expressed%20its%20inability%20recently%20to%20continue%20delivering%20materiel%20to%20its%20many%20clients%2C%20including%20India%2C%20as%20it%20needed%20to%20%E2%80%98prioritise%E2%80%99%20domestic%20military%20manufacturing%20to%20sustain%20domestic%20needs.%20Its%20unstated%20message%20signalled%20the%20urgency%20for%20Russian%20armament%20manufacturers%20to%20ensure%20uninterrupted%20equipment%20supplies%20to%20its%20armed%20forces%20to%20continue%20executing%20their%20deadlocked%20Ukrainian%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20October%2019%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Froe.ru%2Feng%2Fpress-service%2Fpress-releases%2Frosoboronexport-goes-on-to-work-on-technology-partnership-contracts-with-friendly-countries%2F%5C%22%3Epress%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Rosoboronexport%2C%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20dominant%20joint%20stock%20arms%20export%20corporation%2C%20admitted%20to%20currently%20facing%20%E2%80%98pressing%20challenges%E2%80%99.%20Consequently%2C%20in%20a%20departure%20from%20the%20past%20that%20focused%20primarily%20on%20exporting%20equipment%2C%20Rosoboronexport%20offered%20potential%20foreign%20partners%20alternate%20cooperative%20formats%20centred%20on%20technology%20partnerships.%20Military%20and%20defence%20planning%20officials%20in%20New%20Delhi%20fittingly%20interpreted%20this%20admission%20to%20signal%20the%20precipitous%20decline%20of%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20once%20gargantuan%20military%20industry%20which%2C%20almost%20single-handedly%2C%20armed%20India%E2%80%99s%20military%20since%20the%201960s%2C%20especially%20its%20aerial%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20IAF%E2%80%99s%20transport%20fleet%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20earlier%20dominated%20by%20Antonov%20An-32s%20and%20Ilyushin%20Il-76%2C%20had%20undergone%20a%20significant%20makeover%2C%20with%20the%20induction%20of%2011%20Boeing%20C-17%20Globemaster%20III%20and%2012%20Lockheed%20Martin%20C-130J-30%20air%20lifters.%20Another%2056%20C295%20MW%20medium%20transport%20aircraft%20from%20Airbus%20Defence%20and%20Space%20were%20on%20stream%20to%20replace%20the%20IAF%E2%80%99s%20legacy%20Avro-748M%20fleet%2C%20with%2016%20of%20them%20acquired%20in%20flyaway%20condition%20and%2040%20manufactured%20at%20a%20recently%20inaugurated%20facility%20in%20Vadodara%2C%20via%20a%20transfer%20of%20technology.%20And%20though%20some%20100-odd%20An-32s%20continued%20in%20IAF%20service%2C%20their%20%24400%20million%20upgrade%20agreed%20with%20Ukraine%20in%202008%2C%20stands%20suspended%20after%20around%2060%20of%20them%20were%20retrofitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F24171733%2FAntonov_An-32RE_India_-_Air_Force_AN1877310.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F24171733%2FAntonov_An-32RE_India_-_Air_Force_AN1877310.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F24171733%2FAntonov_An-32RE_India_-_Air_Force_AN1877310-300x211.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F24171733%2FAntonov_An-32RE_India_-_Air_Force_AN1877310-1024x719.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-583383%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22842%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Indian%20Air%20Force%E2%80%99s%20Antonov%20An32%20%E2%80%98Cline%E2%80%99%20transport%20aircraft.%20Photo%3A%20Oleg%20V.%20Belyakov%2FWikimedia%20Commons%20CC%20BY%20SA%203.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20in%20early%202019%2C%20the%20IAF%20began%20replacing%20its%20dwindling%20fleet%20of%208-10%20Mil%20Mi-25%2F35%20attack%20helicopters%20with%2022%20Boeing%20AH-64E%20Apache%20equivalents%20that%20were%20acquired%20alongside%2015%20Boeing%20CH-47F%20Chinook%20heavy-lift%20helicopters.%20Both%20latter%20rotary%20aircraft%20were%20shortlisted%20after%20besting%20comparable%20Russian%20platforms%20in%20user%20trials.%20The%20Indian%20Army%20(IA)%20too%20is%20scheduled%20to%20take%20delivery%20in%20early%202024%20of%20the%20first%20of%20six%20Apaches%20it%20had%20signed%20up%20to%20acquire%20in%202020%20for%20around%20%24500%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20decades-old%20defence%20ties%20with%20Moscow%20have%20plateaued%20and%20are%20now%20on%20the%20downswing%2C%20especially%20with%20regard%20to%20military%20aircraft%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Amit%20Cowshish%2C%20former%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20(MoD)%20advisor%20on%20acquisitions.%20The%20materiel%20road%20for%20India%2C%20he%20added%2C%20now%20leads%20fortuitously%20to%20Western%20vendors%20and%20towards%20fast-tracking%20%3Cem%3Eatmanirbharta%3C%2Fem%3E%20(self-reliance)%20to%20indigenously%20develop%20weapon%20systems%20and%20platforms%2C%20or%20to%20a%20practical%20blend%20of%20the%20two%2C%20underscored%20by%20technology%20transfers.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20being%20said%2C%20Moscow%20undoubtedly%20takes%20commercial%20solace%20from%20the%20reality%20that%20some%2060%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20overall%20in-service%20military%20kit%20was%20Russian%20in%20origin%2C%20even%20though%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20materiel%20imports%20from%20Russia%20between%202017%20and%202022%20had%20dropped%20from%2062%25%20to%2045%25%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Stockholm%20International%20Peace%20Research%20Institute.%20But%20the%20IAF%2C%20the%20IN%20and%20to%20a%20large%20extent%20even%20the%20IA%20remain%20heavily%20dependent%20on%20Moscow%20to%20technically%20support%20their%20swathe%20of%20Russian%20fixed-wing%20and%20rotary%20aircraft%2C%20which%20are%20expected%20to%20remain%20in%20service%20for%20at%20least%20two%20decades%20or%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20prominent%20amongst%20these%20were%20the%20IAF%E2%80%99s%20260-odd%20twin-engine%20Sukhoi%20Su-30MKI%20(India)%20multi-role%20fighters%20and%20some%2065%20retrofitted%20MiG-29UPG%20air%20superiority%20combat%20aircraft%20that%20presently%20constitute%20the%20%E2%80%98sword-arm%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20IAF%E2%80%99s%20combat%20squadrons.%20And%2C%20in%20September%20the%20MoD%20had%2C%20after%20extended%20deliberation%2C%20approved%20the%20procurement%20of%2012%20HAL-built%20Su-30MKIs%20as%20replacements%20for%20an%20equal%20number%20lost%20over%20years%20in%20accidents.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20a%20cursory%20evaluation%20of%20the%20steady%20drawdown%20of%20Russian-origin%20aerial%20military%20platforms%20by%20the%20IAF%20and%20IN%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20is%20instructive.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202006%2C%20the%20IAF%20retired%20its%20fabled%20Cold%20War-era%20MiG-25%20%E2%80%98Foxbat%E2%80%99%20supersonic%20interceptor%20and%20reconnaissance%20platform%2C%20nick-named%20Garuda%20after%20the%20mythological%20bird-like%20creature%20from%20Hindu%20scriptures%2C%20whose%20purported%20activities%20were%20as%20mysterious%20and%20enigmatic%20as%20those%20of%20this%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThereafter%2C%20in%20March%202007%20it%20phased%20out%20some%20120%20MiG23MF%2FBN%20%E2%80%98Flogger%E2%80%99%20air%20defence%20and%20ground%20attack%20variant%20fighters%20%E2%80%93%20christened%20Bahadur%20by%20HAL%2C%20followed%2012%20years%20later%2C%20in%20late%202019%2C%20by%20retiring%20its%20last%20upgraded%20MiG-27%20ML%20%E2%80%98swing-wing%E2%80%99%20combat%20aircraft%2C%20of%20which%20some%20165%20examples%20were%20licence-built%20by%20HAL.%20Around%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20IN%20bid%20farewell%2C%20after%2029%20years%2C%20to%20eight%20of%20its%20four-engine%20Tupolev-142MK-Es%2C%20possibly%20one%20of%20the%20best%20maritime%20reconnaissance%20and%20anti-submarine%20warfare%20aircraft%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20India%20has%20also%20bypassed%20Russia%20on%20recent%20aircraft%20contracts%2C%20with%20the%20MoD%20more%20or%20less%20scrapping%20the%20over%20%241.2%20billion%20tender%20from%202014%20for%20200%20Russian%20Kamov%20Ka-226T%20%E2%80%98Hoodlum%E2%80%99%20light%20utility%20helicopters.%20Of%20these%2C%20135%20were%20intended%20for%20the%20Army%20Aviation%20Corps%20and%2065%20for%20the%20IAF%2C%20but%20over%20years%20of%20negotiations%2C%20the%20deal%20became%20mired%20in%20a%20myriad%20of%20insoluble%20complications%20over%20technology%20transfer%20to%20HAL%20and%20overall%20cost%2C%20and%20was%20abandoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20IAF%20was%20also%20sidestepping%20Russia%20in%20upgrading%2084%20of%20its%20Su-30MKIs%20to%20%E2%80%98Super%20Sukhoi%E2%80%99%20standards%2C%20in%20its%20first%20retrofit%20tranche%2C%20by%20enhancing%20their%20overall%20operational%20performance%2C%20to%20keep%20them%20in%20service%20till%202045-50.%20Negotiations%20for%20the%20Su-30MKIs%20retrofit%20by%20HAL%20and%20a%20consortium%20of%20local%20vendors%20which%20includes%20upgrading%20some%2051%20of%20the%20fighters%20operating%2C%20offensive%2C%20surveillance%20and%20detection%20systems%2C%20but%20not%20their%20Al-31F%20engines%20were%20initiated%20with%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20United%20Aircraft%20Corporation%20(UAC)%20and%20Sukhoi%20Corporation%20in%202011%2C%20but%20these%20rumbled%20on%20for%20years%2C%20before%20being%20recently%20abandoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20yet%20another%20telling%20indicator%20of%20the%20IAF%E2%80%99s%20disillusionment%20with%20Russian%20military%20aircraft%2C%20was%20its%20reported%20%E2%80%98unenthusiasm%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98disinterest%E2%80%99%20in%20even%20evaluating%20UAC%20and%20Sukhoi%20Corporation%E2%80%99s%20offer%20of%20MiG-35%20%E2%80%98Fulcrum-F%E2%80%99%20and%20Su-35%20%E2%80%98Flanker-E%E2%80%99%20for%20its%20proposed%20procurement%20of%20114%20multi-role%20fighter%20aircraft%20(MRFA).%20Both%20Russian%20manufacturers%20had%2C%20alongside%20five%20other%20overseas%20original%20equipment%20manufacturers%20(OEMs)%2C%20responded%20to%20the%20IAF%E2%80%99s%20April%202018%20request%20for%20information%20or%20RfI%20for%20the%20planned%20MRFA%20buy%20to%20bolster%20its%20depleting%20fighter%20squadron%20numbers%20that%20had%20declined%20to%20around%2029-30%20from%20a%20sanctioned%20strength%20of%2042%20squadrons.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESenior%20IAF%20and%20industry%20officials%20are%20believed%20to%20have%20reasoned%20that%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20operational%2C%20availability%20and%20sustainability%20considerations%2C%20even%20evaluating%20the%20two%20fuel-intensive%20Russian%20fighter%20types%20for%20eventual%20acquisition%2C%20was%20%E2%80%98irrational%20and%20unworkable%E2%80%99%2C%20categorically%20precluding%20Moscow%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20the%20lucrative%20contract.%20The%20other%20OEM%20responders%20to%20the%20IAFs%20MRFA%20RfI%20included%20France%E2%80%99s%20Dassault%20(Rafale)%2C%20Eurofighter%20(Typhoon)%2C%20Sweden%E2%80%99s%20Saab%20(Gripen-E)%20and%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20Boeing%20and%20Lockheed%20Martin%20(F%2FA-18%20and%20the%20upgraded%20F-21).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20the%20IN%20too%20was%20in%20the%20process%20of%20edging%20away%20from%20inducting%20Russian%20fighters%20into%20its%20new%20aircraft%20carrier%E2%80%99s%20combat%20air%20arm.%20Currently%2C%20it%20was%20in%20advanced%20negotiations%20to%20acquire%2026%20French%20Rafale%20(Marine)%20fighters%20for%20INS%20Vikrant%2C%20instead%20of%20supplementary%20Russian%20MiG-29K%2FKUBs%2C%20all%20of%20which%20had%20collectively%20proven%20operationally%20inefficient%20and%20hugely%20problematic%20since%20their%20commissioning%20into%20service%20from%202009%20onwards.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20IN%20had%20acquired%2045%20twin-engine%20MiG-29K%2FKUBs%20between%202004%20and%202010%20for%20%242.29%20billion%20but%20presently%20operated%20around%2040%2C%20almost%20half%20of%20which%20were%20believed%20to%20be%20in%20reserve%20because%20of%20their%20dismal%20performance%20and%20inability%20to%20deliver%20their%20weapons%20payload%20to%20their%20stated%20range%20with%20a%20full%20fuel%20load.%20An%20excoriating%20analysis%20by%20the%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20in%202016%20had%20binned%20the%20MiG-29Ks%2C%20whose%20operational%20availability%20between%202014%20and%202016%2C%20he%20revealed%2C%20fluctuated%20from%2015.93%25%20to%2037.63%25%2C%20whilst%20that%20of%20the%20MiG-29KUB%20dual-seat%20trainers%20hovered%20between%2021.2%25%20and%2047.14%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F18142346%2FMig-29K_takeofff_from_INS_Vikrant.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F18142346%2FMig-29K_takeofff_from_INS_Vikrant.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F18142346%2FMig-29K_takeofff_from_INS_Vikrant-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F18142346%2FMig-29K_takeofff_from_INS_Vikrant-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-644580%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20MIG-29k%20takes%20off%20from%20INS%20Vikrant.%20Photo%3A%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20GODL-India%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3ERevealingly%2C%20the%20IN%20is%20also%20believed%20to%20have%20halted%20negotiations%20with%20Russia%20to%20acquire%2010%20additional%20Kamov%20Ka-31%20%E2%80%98Helix%E2%80%99%20airborne%20early%20warning%20(AEW%26amp%3BC)%20helicopters%20for%20%24520%20million%2C%20approved%20by%20the%20MoD%20in%20May%202019%2C%20for%20deployment%20aboard%20Vikrant%2C%20following%20uncertainty%20in%20supplies%20over%20sanctions%20and%20attendant%20knotty%20payment%20mechanisms.%20These%2010%20Ka-31s%20were%20to%20have%20supplemented%2010-12%20similar%20platforms%20in%20service%20with%20the%20IN%20since%202003%2C%20all%20of%20which%20needed%20upgrading%2C%20that%20too%20was%20now%20imperilled%20by%20sanctions%20on%20Russia.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20IN%20had%20acquired%2024%20Lockheed%20Martin%2FSikorsky%20MH-60R%20multirole%20helicopters%20in%20a%20%242.6%20billion%20deal%20agreed%20upon%20in%20early%202020%2C%20deliveries%20of%20which%20were%20ongoing%2C%20further%20diluting%20the%20navy%E2%80%99s%20once-prodigious%20Russian%20rotary%20wing%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20conclusion%2C%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3Edruzhba%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20friendship%20with%20Moscow%20which%20sustained%20prodigious%20bilateral%20military%20commerce%20between%20the%20two%2C%20worth%20over%20%2470%20billion%2C%20seems%20to%20have%20run%20its%20course%20at%20the%20altar%20of%20newly%20emergent%20geopolitical%20configurations%2C%20encompassing%20a%20beleaguered%20Russia%20cementing%20close%20strategic%2C%20political%2C%20diplomatic%2C%20economic%20and%2C%20in%20time%2C%20even%20military%20ties%20with%20India%E2%80%99s%20feared%20foe%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699377754000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F22184843%2FSukhoi_Su-30MKI_India_-_Air_Force_AN1234411.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Findian-armed-forces-russia-supplied-platforms-assets-era-end%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russia%E2%80%99s%20once%20gargantuan%20military%20industry%20almost%20single-handedly%20armed%20India%E2%80%99s%20military%20since%20the%201960s%2C%20especially%20its%20aerial%20requirements.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Findian-armed-forces-russia-supplied-platforms-assets-era-end%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bihar%20Caste%20Survey%20Shows%20Every%20Third%20Family%20Poor%3A%20Nitish%20Announces%20Rs%202%20Lakh%20Aid%2C%20Wants%2075%25%20Reservation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F07214142%2FF-AjAdfbYAA6UOc.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatna%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20another%20shot%20in%20the%20arm%20to%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20demand%20for%20a%20nationwide%20caste%20census%2C%20Bihar%20chief%20minister%20Nitish%20Kumar%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20November%207%2C%20announced%20a%20slew%20of%20welfare%20benefits%20for%20poor%20families%20in%20the%20state%20immediately%20after%20releasing%20the%20socio-economic%20data%20in%20the%20state%20assembly.%20The%20socio-economic%20data%20was%20eagerly%20awaited%20after%20the%20Bihar%20govt%20released%20its%20caste%20survey%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20showed%20that%20about%2094%20lakh%20families%20%E2%80%93%2034.13%25%20of%20the%20total%202.76%20crore%20families%20in%20Bihar%20%E2%80%93%20are%20economically%20poor%20and%20earn%20less%20than%20Rs%206%2C000%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESubsequently%2C%20Nitish%20called%20for%2065%25%20of%20government%20jobs%20and%20education%20to%20be%20reserved%20for%20OBCs%2C%20SCs%20and%20STs.%20Scheduled%20Castes%20should%20have%2020%25%20reservation%2C%20while%20OBCs%20and%20EBCs%20together%20should%20get%2043%25%20reservation%2C%20he%20said.%20The%20remaining%202%25%20should%20be%20reserved%20for%20STs%2C%20the%20chief%20minister%20said.%20With%20the%2010%25%20reservation%20for%20the%20economically%20weaker%20sections%20(EWS)%20among%20the%20upper%20castes%2C%20a%20fourth%20of%20government%20jobs%20and%20seats%20in%20educational%20institutes%20will%20be%20reserved%20if%20the%20move%20is%20implemented.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20chief%20minister%20also%20said%20that%20Rs%202%20lakh%20will%20be%20provided%20as%20a%20one-time%20financial%20assistance%20to%20the%2094%20lakh%20families%20who%20earn%20less%20than%20Rs%206%2C000%20per%20month.%20The%20state%20government%20will%20spend%20Rs%202.5%20lakh%20crore%20over%20the%20next%20five%20years%20for%20the%20economically%20poor%2C%20he%20said.%20Of%20these%20families%2C%20those%20who%20are%20homeless%20will%20be%20provided%20an%20additional%20Rs%2040%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHighest%20poverty%20among%20SCs%2C%20STs%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20highest%20proportion%20of%20poor%20families%20was%20among%20the%20Scheduled%20Castes%20(SC)%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(ST)%2C%20the%20data%20showed.%20Among%20families%20from%20SC%20communities%2C%20which%20constitute%2019.65%25%20of%20the%20total%20population%20in%20the%20state%2C%2042.93%25%20are%20poor.%20Among%20the%20minuscule%20ST%20population%2C%20just%201.68%25%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20population%2C%2042.7%25%20are%20poor.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAbout%2033.16%25%20of%20families%20classified%20as%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%20(OBCs)%20are%20poor%20and%2033.58%25%20of%20families%20classified%20as%20Extremely%20Backward%20Classes%20(EBCs)%20are%20poor%2C%20revealed%20the%20data.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbihar-caste-census-released-at-63-obc-ebc-groups-set-to-take-pole-position-in-state-politics%5C%22%3Ecaste%20data%20of%20the%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20that%20while%20OBCs%20constitute%2027.13%25%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20population%2C%20EBCs%20comprise%2036.01%25.%20Among%20upper%20caste%20families%2C%20who%20constitute%2015%2C52%25%20of%20the%20population%2C%2025.09%25%20are%20poor.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20OBCs%2C%20the%20dominant%20Yadav%20caste%20has%20reported%20the%20highest%20poor%20population.%20A%20third%20of%20Yadavs%2C%20who%20constitute%2014.26%25%20of%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20population%2C%20are%20poor%2C%20the%20report%20says.%20Of%20the%20Kushwaha%20(Koiri)%20caste%2C%2034.32%25%20of%20the%20families%20are%20poor.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20SCs%2C%20Musahars%20have%20the%20worst%20socio-economic%20conditions.%20About%2054.56%25%20of%20the%208%2C73%2C281%20families%20of%20Musahars%20are%20poor.%20Of%20the%20Bhuiyan%20community%2C%2053.55%25%20of%20families%20are%20poor.%20Similarly%2C%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20families%20from%20Dom%20and%20Bhogta%20communities%20are%20living%20in%20poverty.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20upper%20castes%2C%20Bhumihars%20have%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20poor%20families.%20While%20the%20caste%20census%20data%20showed%20that%20Bhumihars%20constitute%202.86%25%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20population%2C%2027.58%25%20of%20them%20are%20poor.%20A%20quarter%20of%20the%20Brahmin%20population%20in%20Bihar%20(3.65%25%20of%20the%20total%20population)%20is%20poor%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%20A%20quarter%20of%20Rajputs%20are%20also%20poor.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMuslim%20communities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20Muslims%2C%20the%20Shershahbadi%20and%20Dhuniya%20communities%20%E2%80%93%20classified%20as%20EBCs%20%E2%80%93%20have%2031.99%25%20and%2031.42%25%20families%20living%20in%20poverty.%20About%2026.77%25%20of%20families%20of%20the%20Momin%20caste%20and%2029.67%25%20of%20families%20of%20Rain%20or%20Kunjra%20are%20also%20poor.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20backward%20classes%2C%20the%20Surjapuri%20Muslims%20have%20the%20highest%20percentage%20of%20poor%20families%20(29.33).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20upper-caste%20Muslims%2C%20about%2025.84%25%20of%20Sheikh%20families%20are%20poor.%20Whereas%20in%20the%20Pathan%20caste%2C%20about%2022.20%25%20of%20the%20families%20are%20poor%20and%2017.61%25%20of%20Syed%20families%20live%20in%20poverty.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fhow-true-is-the-claim-that-bihar-caste-survey-is-promoting-casteism%5C%22%3EHow%20True%20Is%20the%20Claim%20That%20Bihar%20Caste%20Survey%20Is%20%E2%80%98Promoting%20Casteism%E2%80%99%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUpper%20castes%20well%20educated%2C%20represented%20in%20government%20jobs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBihar%20has%20a%20total%20of%2013.07%20crore%20population%2C%20out%20of%20which%2020.47%20lakh%20persons%20are%20in%20government%20jobs.%20Of%20these%2020.49%20lakh%20people%2C%206.41%20lakh%20persons%20are%20from%20upper%20castes%2C%206.21%20lakh%20persons%20are%20from%20OBC%20communities%2C%204.61%20lakh%20persons%20are%20from%20EBC%20communities%2C%202.91%20lakh%20persons%20are%20from%20SC%20communities%20and%2030%2C164%20persons%20are%20from%20ST%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20upper%20castes%20constitute%2015%25%20of%20the%20total%20population%2C%20they%20are%20overrepresented%20in%20government%20jobs%2C%20the%20data%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20education%20front%20too%2C%20backward%20communities%20are%20lagging.%20Among%20upper%20castes%2C%2013.41%25%20are%20graduates.%20Among%20BCs%2C%20just%206.77%25%20are%20while%20just%204.27%25%20of%20EBCs%20are.%20Among%20SCs%2C%20only%203.05%25%20of%20the%20population%20are%20graduates.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBihar%20is%20among%20the%20states%20which%20have%20high%20out-migration%20for%20low-paying%20jobs.%20The%20latest%20data%20revealed%20that%20about%2046%20lakh%20people%20of%20Bihar%20are%20living%20in%20other%20states%20to%20make%20their%20livelihood%2C%20whereas%205.52%20lakh%20people%20are%20living%20outside%20to%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EData%20revealed%20that%20only%2011.44%25%20population%20of%20upper%20castes%20are%20labourers%20and%20masons%2C%20whereas%2013.74%25%20of%20BCs%2C%2018.62%25%20of%20EBCs%2C%2021.38%25%20of%20SCs%20and%2018.51%25%20of%20STs%20are%20working%20as%20labourers%20and%20masons.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENitish%20wants%20to%20hike%20reservation%20to%2065%25%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20socio-economic%20data%20was%20released%2C%20the%20Bihar%20government%20proposed%20to%20increase%20caste-based%20reservations%20in%20education%20and%20government%20jobs.%20Currently%2C%20there%20is%20a%20Supreme%20Court-imposed%20ceiling%20of%2050%25%20reservations%20for%20SCs%2C%20STs%20and%20OBCs.%20Chief%20minister%20Nitish%20Kumar%20has%20proposed%20to%20increase%20the%20reservation%20to%2065%25%20%E2%80%93%20excluding%20the%2010%25%20for%20EWS.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20proposal%2C%20Scheduled%20Castes%20will%20have%2020%25%20reservation%20and%20OBCs%20and%20EBCs%20together%20will%20get%2043%25%20reservation.%20STs%20will%20get%202%25%20reservations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20since%20OBCs%20should%20also%20get%20reservations%20according%20to%20their%20population%2C%20the%2050%25%20ceiling%20should%20be%20abolished%20and%20the%20quota%20should%20be%20increased%20to%2065%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMandal%20parties%20have%20long%20been%20arguing%20that%20a%20proper%20caste%20census%20could%20help%20the%20government%20channel%20welfare%20benefits%20in%20a%20scientific%20way.%20The%20Congress%20too%20has%20joined%20the%20bandwagon%20now%20and%20has%20promised%20to%20conduct%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcongress-caste-census-ideological-unity-opposition%5C%22%3Enationwide%20caste%20census%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20state-level%20caste%20surveys%20on%20the%20lines%20of%20Bihar%20if%20elected%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Claims%20of%20development%20debunked%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEconomists%20say%20that%20the%20poverty%20and%20education%20data%20has%20exposed%20Nitish%20Kumar%E2%80%99s%20claims%20that%20he%20has%20overseen%20development%20in%20his%2015%20years%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENawal%20Kishore%20Chaudhary%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20data%20clearly%20says%20that%20Bihar%20has%20poverty%20and%20unemployment.%20About%2063.74%25%20of%20families%20earn%20less%20than%20Rs%2010%2C000%20per%20month%20%E2%80%93%20which%20means%20they%20are%20not%20earning%20even%20Rs%20500%20daily.%20This%20means%20Bihar%20has%20acute%20poverty.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhatever%20claim%20Nitish%20Kumar%20has%20made%20about%20development%2C%20the%20current%20data%20is%20not%20supporting%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EData%20from%20the%202021%20NITI%20Aayog%E2%80%99s%20Multidimensional%20Poverty%20Index%20(MPI)%20said%20that%2051.91%25%20of%20the%20population%20in%20Bihar%20was%20poor%2C%20the%20highest%20among%20all%20the%20states.%20While%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20report%20took%20many%20indicators%20i