various%20roles%2C%20from%20being%20a%20labourer%20and%20cook%20to%20a%20security%20guard%20and%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F140851%2Fmica-mine-child-labourer-du-science-graduate%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20coal%20mine%20worker%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Fparota-1699017781.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22In%202022%2C%20Diganata%20started%20a%20packaged%20paratha%20business%20DFF%20(Daily%20Fresh%20Food)%20in%20Assam.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Fparota-1699017781.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Fparota-1699017781-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Fparota-1699017781-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Fparota-1699017781-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2Fparota-1699017781-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-333563%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EIn%202022%2C%20Diganta%20started%20a%20packaged%20%3Cem%3Eparatha%3C%2Fem%3E%20business%20DFF%20(Daily%20Fresh%20Food)%20in%20Assam.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20at%20present%2C%20the%2034-year-old%20proudly%20owns%20his%20own%20enterprise%2C%20Daily%20Fresh%20Food%20(DFF)%20%E2%80%94%20a%20food%20venture%20that%20offers%20ready-to-eat%20%3Cem%3Eparatha%3C%2Fem%3Es%20(flatbread).%20Launched%20just%20last%20September%2C%20his%20business%20quickly%20gained%20traction%2C%20with%20him%20now%20selling%20a%20minimum%20of%201%2C500%20%3Cem%3Eparatha%3C%2Fem%3E%20packets%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFrom%20doing%20multiple%20menial%20jobs%20to%20starting%20own%20food%20business%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20completing%20his%20Class%2010%20in%202001%2C%20he%20started%20working%20as%20a%20construction%20labourer%20for%20the%20Border%20Roads%20Organisation%20at%20the%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20border%2C%20which%20earned%20him%20Rs%201%2C200%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDiscontented%20with%20the%20job%2C%20he%20quit%20in%20a%20year%20and%20moved%20to%20Meghalaya%20to%20work%20in%20a%20coal%20mine.%20%E2%80%9CWorking%20in%20coal%20mines%20was%20really%20very%20tough%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20blasting%20operations%20often%20induce%20ground%20vibration%20inside%20the%20mine.%20Strong%20vibrations%20damage%20the%20structure%20and%20result%20in%20ceiling%20collapse.%20We%20frequently%20witnessed%20mishaps.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20continues%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20remember%20it%20was%20the%20day%20of%20%3Cem%3EMaghi%20Purnima%20%3C%2Fem%3E(auspicious%20full%20moon%20day)%20when%20one%20of%20my%20friends%20from%20the%20village%20was%20inside%20the%20coal%20mine.%20Due%20to%20the%20strong%20vibrations%2C%20a%20ceiling%20collapsed%20and%20he%20got%20trapped%20inside.%20We%20later%20found%20him%20dead%3B%20his%20body%20was%20crushed%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Diganta.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EDiganta%20Das%2C%20a%20manual%20labour%20of%20Pkg%20food%20industry%20of%20South%20India%2C%20returned%20home%20during%20Covid%20%26amp%3B%20dared%20to%20open%20small%20packaged%20Parota%20making%20units%20in%20Biswanath%20Chariali%20%26amp%3B%20Lakhimpur%2C%20churning%20out%20avg%201200%20packets%20daily%20at%20each%20centre%20capturing%20market%20from%20Tezpur%20to%20Tinsukia.%201%2F3%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FmBzcV5sdEV%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FmBzcV5sdEV%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Mrinal%20Talukdar%20(%40mrinaltalukdar8)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fmrinaltalukdar8%2Fstatus%2F1640331493384790016%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%2027%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%20%3Cp%3EThis%20incident%20left%20him%20devastated%20and%20he%20decided%20to%20pack%20his%20bag%20and%20go%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%2C%20he%20left%20for%20Sikkim%20where%20he%20started%20working%20again%20as%20a%20construction%20worker.%20After%20two%20more%20years%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20move%20to%20Bengaluru.%20%E2%80%9CMost%20of%20the%20youth%20from%20our%20state%20go%20to%20cities%20like%20Delhi%2C%20Bengaluru%2C%20and%20Pune%20for%20work.%20I%20had%20always%20wanted%20to%20see%20Bengaluru%2C%20so%20I%20moved%20there%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20secured%20the%20work%20of%20a%20security%20guard%20in%20the%20city%20for%20a%20monthly%20salary%20of%20Rs%204%2C500%2C%20but%20amid%20low%20salary%20and%20untimely%20payments%2C%20he%20eventually%20quit%20that%20work%20too.%20%E2%80%9CI%20did%20not%20have%20a%20problem%20in%20working%20hard%2C%20but%20I%20wished%20to%20earn%20a%20decent%20income%20for%20all%20the%20hard%20work%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELater%20on%2C%20Diganta%20worked%20as%20a%20cook%20in%20Guwahati%20until%20he%20secured%20a%20job%20as%20a%20mixing%20man%20in%20a%20food%20manufacturing%20unit%20in%20Mangaluru.%20The%20exposure%20helped%20him%20understand%20the%20nitty-gritty%20of%20the%20food%20production%20industry.%20And%20soon%2C%20he%20was%20offered%20the%20job%20of%20a%20%3Cem%3Eparatha%3C%2Fem%3E%20maker.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJust%20when%20he%20thought%20things%20were%20improving%2C%20he%20met%20with%20an%20accident.%20In%202017%2C%20he%20was%20left%20paralysed%20after%20a%20high-voltage%20electric%20cable%20fell%20on%20him.%20%E2%80%9CI%20had%20to%20return%20to%20my%20village.%20That%20was%20the%20toug